This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on learning distributed representations of natural language documents. It also uses a Denoising Autoencoder as the discriminator network, which is a common technique in natural language processing. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses Generative Adversarial Networks, which is a popular machine learning technique. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves learning representations of documents, which is a common task in AI. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GANs are commonly used in image generation tasks, and the paper proposes a method for generating document representations. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as document representations are often used in information retrieval tasks.
